# ION DEX UI design workflow

- Before any development work, read `docs/00-engineering-standards.md`. Treat it as the development iron law.
- Before frontend/UI work, also read `.cursor/skills/ion-web3-ui/SKILL.md`, `docs/05-product-prd.md`, `docs/06-page-flow-and-user-journeys.md`, and `docs/10-ui-design-route.md`.
- Run `node scripts/dev-preflight.mjs` before implementation when shell access is available. Full verification scripts run it automatically.
- UI work must follow the locked direction: OKX Web3-inspired, dark blue/purple base, cyberpunk neon, glassmorphism, aurora/galaxy motion, thin refined neon borders, and responsive behavior at 375px, 768px, and 1440px.
- Do not add new user-facing `shell`, `draft`, `TBD`, placeholder cards, or `Build Checklist` panels. Replace touched unfinished surfaces with product UI modules from the PRD.
- After UI changes, run encoding, frontend verify, high audit, and the required full verification flow.
